# Accessibility Audit (WCAG 2.2)

## Scanning Methodology

Scan components **directly** using code comprehension — do not rely on regex-based scripts. Follow this structured procedure for each component:

1. **Read the component's HTML template** in full — understand the complete DOM structure
2. **Read the component's TypeScript class** — check `@Input()` bindings, dynamic ARIA attributes, programmatic focus management, conditional rendering (`*ngIf`, `*ngSwitch`)
3. **Walk through WCAG-CHECKLIST.yaml criteria systematically** — evaluate each applicable criterion against the template in context (not pattern matching)
4. **Check parent/child component relationships** — accessible names may come from parent bindings, projected content (`<ng-content>`), or wrapper components
5. **Classify each finding** using the severity calibration and image classification rules below
6. **Self-validate** every finding before reporting (see Self-Validation section)

