## Key WCAG Criteria

| Criterion | Level | Requirement |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| 1.1.1 Non-text Content | A | Images, icons have alt text |
| 1.3.1 Info and Relationships | A | Semantic HTML, table headers |
| 1.4.3 Contrast | AA | 4.5:1 text, 3:1 large text |
| 2.1.1 Keyboard | A | All functionality keyboard accessible |
| 2.4.4 Link Purpose | A | Link text is descriptive |
| 2.4.7 Focus Visible | AA | Focus indicator visible |
| 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value | A | Custom controls have ARIA |

## Image Classification

Do **not** apply a single "missing alt" check to all images. Classify each image into one of three categories and apply the correct remediation:

### Decision Tree

```
Is the image inside a <a>, <button>, or other interactive element?
  → YES: FUNCTIONAL — alt must describe the ACTION (what clicking does)
  → NO: Does the image convey information not available in surrounding text?
    → YES: INFORMATIONAL — alt must describe the CONTENT (what it shows)
    → NO: DECORATIVE — use alt="" and aria-hidden="true"
```

### Classification Reference

| Image Type | Detection Heuristic | Correct Treatment | Example |
|-----------|---------------------|-------------------|---------|
| **Functional** | Inside `<a>`, `<button>`, or interactive element; is the only content conveying the link/button purpose | `alt` describes the **action** | `<button><img src="delete.svg" alt="Delete item"></button>` |
| **Informational** | Chart, graph, photo conveying meaning not in surrounding text | `alt` describes the **content** | `<img src="chart.png" alt="Q4 revenue increased 15% from Q3">` |
| **Decorative** | Layout spacer, background flourish, icon with adjacent text already conveying meaning | `alt=""` + `aria-hidden="true"` | `<img src="divider.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true">` |

### Common Misclassifications to Avoid

- **Logo in a link**: Functional (not decorative) — alt should describe the link destination, e.g., `alt="Home page"`
- **Icon next to text label**: Decorative if text already conveys meaning — use `alt=""` + `aria-hidden="true"`
- **Chart/graph**: Informational — alt must summarize the data; use `aria-describedby` for detailed description
- **Avatar/profile photo**: Informational if it's the primary identifier; decorative if name text is adjacent

## Common Component Patterns

### Tables

```html
<!-- ✅ ACCESSIBLE -->
<table aria-label="Data results">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">Status</th>
      <th scope="col">Name</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <span aria-label="Active status">✓</span>
        <span>Active</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<!-- ❌ VIOLATION - Missing aria-label, icon without text -->
<table>
  <td><span>✓</span></td>
</table>
```

### Forms

```html
<!-- ✅ ACCESSIBLE -->
<label for="email">Email Address</label>
<input type="email" 
       id="email" 
       name="email"
       aria-describedby="email-hint email-error">
<span id="email-hint">Enter your work email</span>
<span id="email-error" role="alert" *ngIf="hasError">
  Valid email required
</span>

<!-- ❌ VIOLATION - No label, using placeholder only -->
<input type="email" placeholder="Email">
```

### Buttons & Icons

```html
<!-- ✅ ACCESSIBLE -->
<button aria-label="Delete item" (click)="onDelete()">
  <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- icon --></svg>
</button>

<!-- ❌ VIOLATION - Icon button without label -->
<button (click)="onDelete()">
  <svg><!-- icon --></svg>
</button>
```

### Dialogs/Modals

```html
<!-- ✅ ACCESSIBLE -->
<div role="dialog" 
     aria-label="Confirm deletion" 
     aria-describedby="dialog-desc"
     aria-modal="true">
  <p id="dialog-desc">Are you sure you want to delete this item?</p>
</div>
```

## Keyboard Navigation

### Requirements
- All interactive elements must be focusable
- Logical tab order (no tabindex > 0)
- No keyboard traps
- Skip links for repetitive content
- Focus visible at all times

```html
<!-- ✅ Skip link for keyboard users -->
<a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>

<!-- ✅ Focus management after route change -->
<main id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
  <!-- Page content -->
</main>
```

## Color & Contrast

### Requirements
- 4.5:1 minimum contrast ratio for normal text
- 3:1 for large text (18pt+ or 14pt bold)
- 3:1 for UI components and graphics
- Color not sole method of conveying information

```css
/* ✅ ACCESSIBLE - Sufficient contrast */
.error-text {
  color: #d32f2f;  /* 4.5:1 on white */
}

/* ❌ VIOLATION - Also needs icon or text pattern */
.status-success { color: green; }
.status-error { color: red; }

/* ✅ ACCESSIBLE - Color + icon */
.status-success::before { content: "✓ "; }
.status-error::before { content: "✗ "; }
```

## Dynamic Content

### Live Regions

```html
<!-- ✅ Announce status updates -->
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="visually-hidden">
  {{ statusMessage }}
</div>

<!-- ✅ Error announcements -->
<div aria-live="assertive" role="alert" *ngIf="errorMessage">
  {{ errorMessage }}
</div>
```

### Loading States

```html
<!-- ✅ ACCESSIBLE loading indicator -->
<div *ngIf="loading" 
     role="status" 
     aria-label="Loading data">
  <span class="visually-hidden">Loading...</span>
</div>
```

