## Self-Validation

Before presenting findings, **self-validate every issue** to reduce false positives:

### Step 1: Re-read in Context
Re-read each flagged location in the **full file context** (not just the flagged line). Check at least 10 lines above and below.

### Step 2: Check False Positive Indicators
Dismiss a finding if any of these apply:
- **Parent/sibling provides label**: A parent `<mat-form-field>` contains `<mat-label>`, or a wrapping `<label>` element exists
- **`*ngIf` / `*ngSwitch` alternative**: A conditional branch provides an accessible version (e.g., `*ngIf="isLoading; else dataTable"`)
- **Custom directive**: A directive like `[appAriaLabel]` or `[cdkAriaLabel]` dynamically sets ARIA attributes
- **Adjacent visible text**: Text adjacent to an icon or image already conveys the same meaning
- **Projected content**: `<ng-content>` slot receives accessible content from the parent component

### Step 3: Assign Confidence
Rate each validated finding:
| Confidence | Meaning | When to Use |
|------------|---------|-------------|
| **High** | Verified violation — no possible provider of accessible name/role | Missing alt with no parent label, keyboard trap confirmed |
| **Medium** | Likely violation — but dynamic binding or runtime state could resolve | `[attr.aria-label]` bound to variable not visible in template |
| **Low** | Possible violation — requires runtime verification | Contrast depends on theme, focus timing not determinable statically |

### Step 4: Suppression Support
Honor `<!-- a11y-ignore: reason -->` comments in templates. When found:
- Exclude the associated element from the violations table
- Include it in the **Reviewed & Dismissed** section with the stated reason
- If the suppression reason is inadequate, note this in the report

## Runtime Validation Guidance

Some issues **cannot be fully verified through static analysis**. Flag these explicitly and provide runtime test guidance.

### Issues Requiring Runtime Tools

| Issue Category | Why Runtime Needed | Recommended Tool |
|---------------|-------------------|------------------|
| Contrast ratios | Depend on computed styles, CSS variables, theme | axe DevTools, Color Contrast Analyser |
| Dynamic content visibility | `*ngIf` toggled content, lazy-loaded modules | Browser DevTools, axe DevTools |
| Focus management | Timing-dependent, route change behavior | Manual keyboard testing |
| Live region announcements | AT + browser combination dependent | JAWS + Chrome, NVDA + Firefox |
| Dialog focus trapping | CDK trap behavior, timing | Manual keyboard testing |

### axe-core Test Snippets

Generate axe-core test snippets for components with Medium/Low confidence findings:

```typescript
import { axe, toHaveNoViolations } from 'jasmine-axe';

beforeEach(() => jasmine.addMatchers(toHaveNoViolations));

it('should pass axe accessibility checks', async () => {
  const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(MyComponent);
  fixture.detectChanges();
  const results = await axe(fixture.nativeElement);
  expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
});
```

### Manual AT Verification Table

Include a manual verification table for findings that require screen reader or keyboard testing:

```markdown
| # | Component | Test With | What to Verify |
|---|-----------|-----------|----------------|
| 1 | DataTable | JAWS + Chrome | Column headers announced when navigating cells |
| 2 | DeleteDialog | Keyboard | Focus moves to dialog on open, returns to trigger on close |
| 3 | StatusBanner | NVDA + Firefox | Live region announces status update on change |
| 4 | SearchFilter | VoiceOver + Safari | Combobox role and expanded state announced |
```

## Severity Calibration

Classify every finding by **user workflow impact**, not just WCAG level.
The key distinction: Critical = **blocks task completion entirely** vs. High = **major usability barrier** the user can still work around.

| Severity | Criteria | Examples |
|----------|----------|---------|
| 🔴 Critical | **Blocks task completion** — prevents screen reader from accessing required content, prevents keyboard-only navigation, prevents form submission or navigation | Keyboard trap with no escape, form cannot be submitted, entire content region invisible to screen reader |
| 🟠 High | **Major usability barrier** — incorrect programmatic structure, incorrect heading structure affecting navigation, missing form labels on required inputs | Missing form labels, missing alt on functional images, incorrect heading hierarchy, missing table headers |
| 🟡 Medium | **Partial compliance** — missing enhancement but workaround exists, improper semantic structure but content still readable | Insufficient contrast, vague link text, missing `aria-sort`, `aria-expanded` missing but state still perceivable |
| 🔵 Low | **Improvement suggestion** — cosmetic issue, best-practice enhancement | Missing skip link on simple page, `role="presentation"` preferred over `aria-hidden` |

> **Calibration note:** Missing form labels and missing alt on functional images are **High**, not Critical, because the user can still navigate the page — they just can't determine the control's purpose. Critical is reserved for issues that make a workflow **completely impassable** (e.g., keyboard trap, entire region hidden from AT).

## Report Format

```markdown
# Accessibility Audit

**Status**: ✅ COMPLIANT / ❌ VIOLATIONS FOUND
**WCAG Level**: AA
**Components Audited**: X components

## Issues Found

| Sev | Issue | WCAG | Evidence | AT Impact | Fix |
|-----|-------|------|----------|-----------|-----|
| 🔴 Critical | Keyboard trap in modal | 2.1.2 (F10) | `<div (click)="close()">` at dialog.html:12 — no keyboard handler | Keyboard user cannot escape modal; must reload page | Add `(keydown.escape)="close()"` and `cdkTrapFocus` |
| 🟠 High | Image missing alt | 1.1.1 (F65) | `<img src="chart.png">` at dashboard.html:45 | JAWS announces "image" with no context; user cannot determine chart content | Add `alt="Q4 revenue trend showing 15% increase"` |
| 🟡 Medium | Insufficient contrast | 1.4.3 | `.hint-text { color: #999 }` at styles.scss:88 — ratio 2.8:1 on #fff | Low-vision users cannot read hint text | Change to `color: #767676` (4.5:1) |
| 🔵 Low | Missing skip link | 2.4.1 | No skip link in app.component.html | Keyboard users must tab through nav on every page | Add `<a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>` |

## Recommendations
1. [Specific, actionable fix per issue — included in table above]

## Reviewed & Dismissed
Issues suppressed via `<!-- a11y-ignore: reason -->` or dismissed during self-validation.

| Location | Suppression Reason | Reviewer |
|----------|--------------------|----------|
| dialog.html:5 | `<!-- a11y-ignore: label provided by parent component binding -->` | Agent self-validation |

**Screen Reader Tested**: Yes/No
**Keyboard Navigation Tested**: Yes/No
```
